</pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="cp">&lt;!doctype html&gt;</span> <span class="c">&lt;!-- instruction to the browser about what version of HTML the page is written in.--&gt;</span>
<span class="nt">&lt;html&gt;</span>
  <span class="nt">&lt;head&gt;</span> <span class="c">&lt;!-- title,scripts, styles, meta information, and more. --&gt;</span>
    <span class="nt">&lt;meta</span> <span class="na">charset=</span><span class="s">"UTF-8"</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span>
    <span class="nt">&lt;title&gt;</span>Sample<span class="nt">&lt;/title&gt;</span>
  <span class="nt">&lt;/head&gt;</span>

  <span class="nt">&lt;body&gt;</span>
  <span class="c">&lt;!-- Content of the Body --&gt;</span>
  <span class="nt">&lt;/body&gt;</span>
<span class="nt">&lt;/html&gt;</span>
</pre></td></tr></tbody></table></code></pre></figure>

<p>The <code class="highlighter-rouge">&lt;head&gt;</code> contains <code class="highlighter-rouge">meta</code> information about the page, information the browser needs before rendering it. While the <code class="highlighter-rouge">&lt;body&gt;</code> contains the actual viewable contents of the page.</p>

<p>Here are some common html tags:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-html" data-lang="html"><table class="rouge-table"><tbody><tr><td class="gutter gl"><pre class="lineno">1
