</pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="c">&lt;!-- Headlines --&gt;</span>
<span class="nt">&lt;h1&gt;</span>Header 1<span class="nt">&lt;/h1&gt;</span>
<span class="nt">&lt;h2&gt;</span>Header 2<span class="nt">&lt;/h2&gt;</span>

<span class="c">&lt;!-- Paragraph --&gt;</span>
<span class="nt">&lt;p&gt;</span>paragraph<span class="nt">&lt;/p&gt;</span>

<span class="c">&lt;!-- Lists --&gt;</span>
<span class="nt">&lt;ul&gt;</span> <span class="c">&lt;!-- Unordered Lists --&gt;</span>
  <span class="nt">&lt;li&gt;</span>List Item 1<span class="nt">&lt;/li&gt;</span>
  <span class="nt">&lt;li&gt;</span>List Item 2<span class="nt">&lt;/li&gt;</span>
<span class="nt">&lt;/ul&gt;</span>

<span class="nt">&lt;ol&gt;</span> <span class="c">&lt;!-- Ordered Lists --&gt;</span>
  <span class="nt">&lt;li&gt;</span>List Item 1<span class="nt">&lt;/li&gt;</span>
  <span class="nt">&lt;li&gt;</span>List Item 2<span class="nt">&lt;/li&gt;</span>
<span class="nt">&lt;/ol&gt;</span>

<span class="c">&lt;!-- Images --&gt;</span>
<span class="nt">&lt;img</span> <span class="na">alt=</span><span class="s">"Tech SoA Logo"</span> <span class="na">src=</span><span class="s">"http://tech.soa.cmu.edu/img/favicon.png"</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span>

<span class="c">&lt;!-- Links --&gt;</span>
<span class="nt">&lt;a</span> <span class="na">href=</span><span class="s">"http://tech.soa.cmu.edu"</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span> Here be a link <span class="nt">&lt;/a&gt;</span>
</pre></td></tr></tbody></table></code></pre></figure>

<p>Mozilla has great <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element">documentation</a> that outlines many of the HTML elements, play and browse!</p>

<p>Now that we know some of the basics lets create a simple page. Create a page with <code class="highlighter-rouge">meta</code> description, nav bar, some body content with a couple elements from above or from the Mozilla docs and a footer. Rock and roll!</p>

