<h3 id="colors">Colors</h3>

<p>You are probably thinking there are real color names in css? How is that possible? Well many have been included with the language, that being said you can also use <code class="highlighter-rouge">hex</code>, <code class="highlighter-rouge">rgba</code> and a couple other formats. For a full list of supported colors check this <a href="https://www.w3schools.com/colors/colors_names.asp">out</a>. And if you are looking for some other awesome colors check out <a href="http://qulr.life">Qulr.life</a>.</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-css" data-lang="css"><table class="rouge-table"><tbody><tr><td class="gutter gl"><pre class="lineno">1
