</pre></td></tr></tbody></table></code></pre></figure>

<h3 id="padding--margin">Padding &amp; Margin</h3>

<p>The short answer is margin is on the exterior of a container and padding on the interior. Creating a exterior buffer and interior duffer respectively. Hoepfully the image of Paddington Bear helps, get it get it 😜 ? Padding-ton</p>

<p><img src="/img/html-css-little-deeper/padding-margin.png" alt="Padding or Margin?" /></p>

<p>Now lets style some pages! Play with nesting of elements, importing a font or 2, adjust colors and add a hover effect or 2. And if you are feeling adventurous check out what a <code class="highlighter-rouge">@media</code> query does, this <a href="https://www.w3schools.com/css/css_rwd_mediaqueries.asp">link</a> might help. Use it to create a breakpoint and start thinking responsively. Happy deving! Also check out <a href="http://caniuse.com">can i use</a> to see if a css property is supported by a certain browser.</p>
